<div id="banner">
	<h1>RSS 3.0 Update</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Thanks for all the great feedback on RSS 3.0. I&#8217;ve been in New York the past few days, but I&#8217;ll try to process it all ASAP. I&#8217;m also <a href="http://scriptingnews.userland.com/backissues/2002/09/10#When:7:23:51AM">pushing back removing the disclaimers on the spec by 24 hours</a>.</p>

<p>Thanks to Sean B. Palmer, my eye in the sky, for sending me a whole batch of updates <a href="000574">to my RSS 3.0 info page</a>. There&#8217;s some great feedback and a new feed.</p>

<p>Thanks to everyone for your help, it&#8217;s been a lot of fun.</p>

<p>Watch this space for spec updates&#8230;</p>

<p>I&#8217;ve changed it to use the language tag syntax of RFC 3066 thanks to a suggestion from Sean M. Burke.</p>

